One of the most rewarded applications of AACP is believed to be used as cool roofing materials. The real-world aging of cool roofing materials mainly includes soiling and weathering. Soiling mainly results from the deposition of airborne carbon black, dust, particulate organic matter (POM) and microbial growth. Weathering is mainly from exposure to UV irradiation of natural sunlight, accompanied by moisture and temperature variation of day and night. It takes quite a long time, usually several years, for the roofing materials to reach a quasi-steady state of R̅solar and ε¯LWIR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
