Different from simulated aging, the real-world aging is more complex. The soiling and weathering are synergistic to promote the course of aging39. To make up for the limitation of simulated aging, we performed over 6 months long outdoor exposure in Chengdu (humid and hot climate) and Xi’an (dry and hot climate) of China to test the durability of the coatings against real-world aging (Fig. 4a, b, and Supplementary Fig. 25). All coating slides were split into three regions: unexposed/(exposed, washed)/(exposed, unwashed). The ε¯LWIR\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
